Look, if someone on Twitter or Discord says that he is an expert day trader=
 who has made millions trading penny stocks and will teach you his secrets,=
 then I can tell you his secret. Here it is:
=09He buys penny stocks.=09Then he goes on Twitter and Discord and tells yo=
u=C2=A0to buy them because they are so good and will go up.=09You =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0and his other Twitter followers =E2=80=94 buy them, which makes them =
go up.=09He sells them to you at a profit.=09Then you are stuck with them. =
They are not in fact good =E2=80=94=C2=A0they just went up because he told =
you to buy them =E2=80=94 and you end up selling them at a loss.=09He posts=
 pictures of himself standing next to Ferraris, to validate his multimillio=
naire-day-trader status.=09Other people see the Ferraris=C2=A0and want to g=
et into the game.=09He repeats this process.=09In the fullness of time, the=
 US Securities and Exchange Commission and federal prosecutors notice.=09Th=
ey go find his chats and emails and maybe surreptitiously record some of hi=
s private conversations.=09In all of those chats he turns out to have said =
things like =E2=80=9CI love doing crime=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Clook at me do=
ing all these crimes=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cthis stuff I am doing is market =
manipulation, a crime=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Ccrime crime crime crime crime c=
rime,=E2=80=9D but with more swearing.=09The prosecutors and SEC bring frau=
d charges.=09In a sense, the complaints are very boring, because this is th=
e most obvious sort of financial crime, and every case is exactly the same.=
=09In another sense, the complaints are entertaining, because of the chats.

This is called a =E2=80=9Cpump-and-dump.=E2=80=9D I don=E2=80=99t know why =
people keep falling for it? I guess the pictures of the Ferraris. Also a de=
sire for investing to be easy, for it to be a=C2=A0trick=C2=A0that you can =
learn from some clever insiders on a Discord. If I tell you =E2=80=9Cbuying=
 stock is about allocating capital to productive businesses and sharing, ov=
er the long term, in the value they create for society,=E2=80=9D and some g=
uy standing next to a Ferrari on Twitter says =E2=80=9Cbuying stocks is abo=
ut interpreting mysterious signals that tell you THIS STOCK WILL GO UP 200%=
 THIS AFTERNOON,=E2=80=9D his theory sounds more fun, and it certainly soun=
ds like it will make you more money more quickly than my theory. It=C2=A0wi=
ll=C2=A0make=C2=A0him=C2=A0more money more quickly. Like, the guy=C2=A0is=
=C2=A0a successful day trader. It=E2=80=99s just that his secret is trickin=
g you.
I say =E2=80=9Cyou,=E2=80=9D but I doubt anyone reading this column is actu=
ally getting tricked. This whole online subculture =E2=80=94=C2=A0people wh=
o go on Twitter and Discord so they can be tricked by pump-and-dump scammer=
s =E2=80=94=C2=A0is quite large and very hard for me to understand. My assu=
mption is that a lot of them think they are wise to the scam. If some pump-=
and-dump scammer pumps a stock, and you buy it a second after he pumps it a=
nd sell it a second before he dumps it, you can make money alongside him. Y=
ou are knowingly playing hot potato; you are trying to follow his lead to t=
ake advantage of his=C2=A0other=C2=A0victims. Perhaps this will work, or pe=
rhaps it won=E2=80=99t and you=E2=80=99ll end up a victim too, but maybe it=
 beats having a real job.=C2=A0
Anyway:

The Securities and Exchange Commission today announced charges against eigh=
t individuals in a $100 million securities fraud scheme in which they used =
the social media platforms Twitter and Discord to manipulate exchange-trade=
d stocks.
According to the SEC, since at least January 2020, seven of the defendants =
promoted themselves as successful traders and cultivated hundreds of thousa=
nds of followers on Twitter and in stock trading chatrooms on Discord. Thes=
e seven defendants allegedly purchased certain stocks and then encouraged t=
heir substantial social media following to buy those selected stocks by pos=
ting price targets or indicating they were buying, holding, or adding to th=
eir stock positions. However, as the complaint alleges, when share prices a=
nd/or trading volumes rose in the promoted securities, the individuals regu=
larly sold their shares without ever having disclosed their plans to dump t=
he securities while they were promoting them.
"As our complaint states, the defendants used social media to amass a large=
 following of novice investors and then took advantage of their followers b=
y repeatedly feeding them a steady diet of misinformation, which resulted i=
n fraudulent profits of approximately $100 million," said Joseph Sansone, C=
hief of the SEC Enforcement Division=E2=80=99s Market Abuse Unit. "Today=E2=
=80=99s action exposes the true motivation of these alleged fraudsters and =
serves as another warning that investors should be wary of unsolicited advi=
ce they encounter online."

There are also  federal criminal charges in Texas. The SEC complaint gives =
each defendant his online nickname, like a Mafia indictment but much less i=
ntimidating:
EDWARD CONSTANTIN, a/k/a =E2=80=9CMrZackMorris,=E2=80=9D a/k/a =E2=80=9CEdw=
ard Constantinescu,=E2=80=9D PERRY MATLOCK, a/k/a =E2=80=9CPJ Matlock,=E2=
=80=9D THOMAS COOPERMAN, a/k/a =E2=80=9CTommy Coops,=E2=80=9D GARY DEEL, a/=
k/a =E2=80=9CMystic Mac,=E2=80=9D MITCHELL HENNESSEY, a/k/a =E2=80=9CHugh H=
enne,=E2=80=9D STEFAN HRVATIN, a/k/a =E2=80=9CLadeBackk,=E2=80=9D DANIEL KN=
IGHT, a/k/a =E2=80=9CDeity of Dips,=E2=80=9D and JOHN RYBARCYZK, a/k/a =E2=
=80=9CUltra Calls,=E2=80=9D a/k/a =E2=80=9CThe Stock Sniper,=E2=80=9D Defen=
dants.
They were on Twitter, they had Discord forums called Atlas Trading and Sapp=
hire Trading, they had a podcast:
In July 2020, Knight and Hennessey launched a podcast called =E2=80=9CPenni=
es: Going in Raw=E2=80=9D (=E2=80=9CPGIR=E2=80=9D). PGIR bills itself as an=
 informational podcast =E2=80=9C[d]iscussing volume, price targets, penny s=
tocks, accumulation, reverse splits and much more=E2=80=9D and claims to be=
 the =E2=80=9C#1 Stock Market Podcast in America=E2=80=9D with over 2.3 mil=
lion downloads.=C2=A0
